<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1570" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1570">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/410.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Authorization is requested by the supervisory committee to call upon
                            Tenth Infantry Regiment and Marines Battalion in case, contrary to
                            expectations, their assistance should become necessary to preserve order
                            in Panama City and Colon on election days, June 30 and July 14.
                            Committee recommends withdrawal of marines from the Isthmus should not
                            take place before July 14.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>